genresAdvancedInfo.name: swiss folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Swiss folk music is a genre that celebrates the rich cultural heritage of Switzerland. It features traditional instruments such as the accordion, the dulcimer, and the alphorn, and often incorporates yodeling and other vocal techniques. Swiss folk music is an important part of Swiss culture, and is often performed at festivals and events throughout the country.
